Imagine you are building an E-commerce API.

Without Spring Boot you must:

1️⃣ Configure server
2️⃣ Configure dependencies
3️⃣ Configure database
4️⃣ Configure web framework
-----------------------------------------
With Spring Boot:

Just write:

@RestController
public class HelloController {

    @GetMapping("/hello")
    public String hello(){
        return "Hello World";
    }

}

Run the app → API works.
----------------------------------
When Spring Boot runs:

Your Code
   ↓
Spring Boot
   ↓
Spring Framework
   ↓
Embedded Server (Tomcat)
   ↓
Application Running

Default server used:

👉 Apache Tomcat
----------------------
Spring Boot Architecture (Simple)

Main components:

1️⃣ Controller
2️⃣ Service
3️⃣ Repository
4️⃣ Database

Architecture:

Client (Browser/Postman)
        ↓
Controller
        ↓
Service
        ↓
Repository
        ↓
Database
